-- MOVES-Cordea Savills names Cristiano Ronchi head of investment, Italy 
-- 
-- Tue Dec 16, 2014 08:06AM EST
-- None



Dec 16 (Reuters) - Property investment manager Cordea Savills named Cristiano Ronchi as head of investment, Italy, and a member of the board of the Italian regulated entity, Cordea Savills SGR.

Ronchi most recently worked in the role of director of investments, Cordea Savills, Milan. He joined the company in 2005 as portfolio manager for Pan-European Funds.